                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/24013: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Nogales</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dyer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-21T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 21, 1920—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your May 18, 10 A.M.</p>
                <p>You will exercise caution in your dealings with Governor, and take no steps which
                    may, even by implication, be construed as recognition by any officer of this
                    Government of the new régime. Department <pb facs="0266" n="166" xml:id="pg_166"
                    /> directs your attention to fact that information given out, and requests made,
                    by Governor of Sonora do not always accord with program of persons now in
                    control at Mexico City.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
